name: r-pkgnet
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.4.2" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-pkgnet
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/pkgnet_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/pkgnet/pkgnet_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7bbf5dab94463e6e07d1f51da5b9f161fd5b6ac91ef9e8ad7e0a2063f52d2b78

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dt
    - r-r6
    - r-assertthat
    - r-covr
    - r-data.table
    - r-futile.logger
    - r-glue
    - r-igraph
    - r-knitr
    - r-magrittr
    - r-rlang
    - r-rmarkdown >=1.9
    - r-visnetwork
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dt
    - r-r6
    - r-assertthat
    - r-covr
    - r-data.table
    - r-futile.logger
    - r-glue
    - r-igraph
    - r-knitr
    - r-magrittr
    - r-rlang
    - r-rmarkdown >=1.9
    - r-visnetwork

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('pkgnet')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('pkgnet')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/UptakeOpenSource/pkgnet, https://uptakeopensource.github.io/pkgnet/
  license: BSD_3_clause
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Tools from the domain of graph theory can be used to quantify the complexity and vulnerability to failure of a software package. That is the guiding philosophy of this package. 'pkgnet' provides tools to analyze the dependencies between functions in an R package and between its imported packages.
  license_family: BSD

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
